[DERIVED] Derived Nervous System Finding

Source: R/data.R
NV.Rd

Nervous system finding derived dataset.

Usage

data(NV)

Format

A data frame with 4480 observations and 20 variables.

Source

For more details see the help vignette: vignette(topic = 'ADNIMERGE2-Derived-Data', package = 'ADNIMERGE2')

Details

  • STUDYID character Study Identifier ; , with character options: ADNI

  • DOMAIN character Domain Abbrevation , with character options: NV

  • USUBJID character Unique Subject Identifier

  • NVSEQ integer Sequence Number Range value: 1, ..., 14

  • NVLNKID character Link ID

  • NVTESTCD character Short Name of Nervous System Test , with character options: AMYSTAT, FDGMROI, PIB

  • NVTEST character Name of Nervous System Test , with character options: Amyloid Status - Clinician Judgment, FDG-PET metaROI 8mm, Average PIB PET SUVr

  • NVCAT character Category for Nervous System , with character options: AMYLOID STATUS, FDG-8MM, PIBPETSV

  • NVSTRESC character Character Result/Finding in Std Format

  • NVSTRESN numeric Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units Range value: 0.566896551724138, ..., 2.9275

  • NVSTRESU character Standard Units , with character options: RATIO

  • NVMETHOD character Method of Test or Examination , with character options: PET, FDGPET, PET SCAN

  • NVBLFL character Baseline Flag , with character options: Yes

  • NVDRVFL character Derived Flag , with character options: Yes

  • VISITNUM numeric Visit Number Range value: 1, ..., 46

  • VISIT character Visit Name

  • VISITDY numeric (Planned*) Study Day of Visit Range value: -106, ..., 6912

  • EPOCH character Epoch , with character options: Baseline, Follow-up

  • NVDTC Date Date/Time of Collection Date: YYY-MM-DD

  • NVDY numeric Study Day of Collection Range value: -106, ..., 6912
